{% layout "work" %}
{% block content %}
<header class="clearfix">
  <section>
      <img src="{{"smallpeeps_opening.png" | asset_url }}" alt="Michael Cattell Home Icon" />
  </section>
</header>

<section class="contentinternalpadeven">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="twelve columns">
          <h2>About the project</h2>
          <p><a href="http://www.smallpeeps.com" title="view small peeps website here">www.smallpeeps.com</a></p>
          <p class="intro">“A group of passionate moms who want to find quality products.”<br>
          A great new start up of a friend of mine, selling all things for kids: from party favours to one off gifts.</p>
          <p class="intro">One word – fun!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
 
<section class="contentnopad">
  <div class="contentinternalpadeven">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="six columns">
        <h3 class="standardh3">My Role</h3>
        <p class="intro">Design logo and personalize ‘off-the-shelf’ bought shop (for e-commerce). Also assist in teaching how to use backend of shop and advise on SEO techniques.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="six columns">
           <img src="{{"smallpeeps_role.png" | asset_url }}" alt="Michael Cattell Home Icon" id="object" />
      </div>      
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content">
  <div class="contentinternalpadeven">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="twelve columns">
        <h3 class="standardh3">The Layout</h3>
        <p class="intro">From the previous layout, I decided it would be easier to do a more clean and simple approach to help the user buy more than one product, thus implementing featured products section and a carousel. </p>
      </div> 
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<section class="contentnopad fadeInImg animated">
    <div class="row width1100">  
      <img src="{{"smallpeeps_layout.jpg" | asset_url }}" alt="Michael Cattell Home Icon" id="object1"/>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="contentnopad">
  <div class="contentinternalpadeven">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="six columns fadeInImg animated">
        <img src="{{"smallpeeps_birds.jpg" | asset_url }}" alt="" id="object2"/>
      </div>      
      <div class="six columns">
        <h3 class="standardh3">Is it a bird..well no, it’s a logo</h3>
        <p class="intro">The request was to do a logo which was ‘youthful but smart enough to go inside a boutique..oh and also a bird within the logo due to the naming of ‘Peeps’, of course I happily obliged – I haven’t drawn a bird in years!</p>
      </div>      
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="contentnopad">
  <div class="contentinternalpadeven">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="twelve columns">
        <h3 class="standardh3">Putting it all together</h3>
        <p class="intro">All that had to be done regarding the print side was update my previously designed business cards, product tags and complement slips (when ordered online) with the new logo. The website was more tricky, personalizing quite a rigid template with tiny improvements (carousel, free postage sticker, featured products section and making it look cuter) alongside a quite tutorial on best practices and use of the admin section.</p>
      </div>
   
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

